item.title: forschung
item.description:
Research Programme

The main focus of our research is the research programme of the areas 1 and 2, that has been developed by players of science and economy. Here we investigate critical issues along the value chains of plant derived feed and food (green value chain) and animal derived food (red value chain). By applying scientific methods we explore how to improve production of feeds and foods.

Area 3 bundles our strategic research and is an innovation platform for development of advanced technologies. Our strategic research is focused on basic research and - based on the results - development of advanced and universally applicable technologies für improved and quicker controls of hygiene, quality and authenticity along the value chains of plant- and amnimal derived feed and food of areas 1 and 2.

item.title: Area 1 - Agrifood
item.description:
The green value chain

Scientific innovations for plant derived feed and food.

In the green area we focus on topics from the cultivation of plants to plant-based feed and food.

We research interaction of microbial communities with plants to improve resistance against plant diseases, sensory properties of vegetables or storage suitability of crops. We investigate advanced technologies for detecting plant diseases, new ways to use plant-based by-products and innovative approaches to produce safe and nutritionally valuable plant derived foods.

item.title: Area 2 - Agrifood
item.description:
The red value chain

Scientific innovations for animal derived food.

In the red area we focus on topics from innovative animal nutrition to healthy preparation techniques.

We seek innovative approaches for feeding, health monitoring and management of livestock, we deal with aspects of raw milk quality, with detection and prevention of microbes that potentially cause food spoilage during processing of milk and meat and we explore healthy ways of food processing, preparation and heating to retain valuable ingredients and improve the nutrtional value of foods.

item.title: Area 3 - Agrifood
item.description:
Blue sky innovations

For quality from field to fork.

In the blue area we do basic research and hence develop modern and universally applicable technologies. We apply multichemical fingerprinting, isotope analysis, new generation sequencing and several spectral methods (spectral sensing, chemical imaging) and explore mycotoxins, their metabolites and their effects. One of our targets is to establish the first isotopic landscape (“isoscape”) of Austria for determination of origin of foods.

item.title: company
item.description:
Mission

We want to make food and food production better, safer and more sustainable

To accomplish this mission, we examine relevant steps along the value chains feed - food and combine the expertise of well-known Austrian research institutions with the know-how of more than 30 innovative enterprises from several countries, with high affinity to research.

  • How is our food produced?

  • Is the production sustainable, the food fresh and free from foreign objects, residuals and contaminations?

  • Are the indications of provenance and quality correct?

  • How can we further reduce the use of pesticides and antibiotics?

  • How can we improve livestock husbandry and feeding of farm animals in a sustainable way?

  • How can we reduce food waste and use valuable ingredients more efficiently?

  • How can we improve nutritional value and sensory properties of foods?

These are questions, that the founders and partners of FFoQSI are scrutinizig for decades, and they do not only concern food producers and processors but increasingly large parts of the public - and quite rightly. Nutrition is a crucial issue.

We promise: we keep at it!

Dr. Jürgen Marchart
Managing Director
 Univ.-Prof. Dr. Martin Wagner
Scientific Diretor

item.title: partner
item.description:
Partner companies

Real innovation often originates from close collaboration of partners at distant positions along a value chain.

Our network offers multiple opportunities for informal and creative exchange with more than 30 companies - innovative start-ups, small and middle sized enterprises up to national and international market leaders - from several countries and positions along the value chains feed-food, who have high affinity for research.

The expertise of our company partners covers the folllowing sectors:

  • production and processing of plant-based foods
  • biotechnological plant protection
  • agricultural engineering, sensor technology, monitoring systems
  • knowledge transfer
  • production of feed and feed additives for farm animals
  • processing of animal derived foods
  • development of new kitchen devices
  • analytics

What does FFoQSI offer?

  • We carry out our research projects in teams of cooperation partners and support them with professional project management.
  • We help to match the appropriate partners, support the planning of the individual research projects and deliver regular progress reports to provide the necessary overview.

We are always interested in new cooperations - just contact us.
